            The aim of my amendment was not simply to provide a hook with which to raise this issue but to make the point that the <a href="/acts/data-protection-act-1984">Data Protection Act</a> does not prevent the dissemination of personal data when that is necessary in the public interest. The problem raised by the noble Baroness, Lady Masham, in relation to that Act was, as I understand it, that the provisions of the Act were misunderstood by the parties involved and that the Act did not prevent the retention and dissemination of the information at issue in that case.</p><p>
